### Build-a-Bank · Step 13 · Spring MVC deep — Problem Details, OpenAPI & Swagger UI
### 1) Start Postgres:  docker compose -f services/demand-account/compose.yaml up -d   (maps host 5433)
### 2) Start the service:
###    SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5433/demand_account ./mvnw -pl services/demand-account spring-boot:run
### 3) Browse Swagger UI:  http://localhost:8082/swagger-ui.html

@host = http://localhost:8082

### The generated OpenAPI 3.1 spec (springdoc) → 200 JSON
GET {{host}}/v3/api-docs

### Swagger UI (browsable client) → 200 HTML
GET {{host}}/swagger-ui/index.html

### Open account A → 201 (note the X-Request-Id + X-Timing-Enabled response headers)
POST {{host}}/api/accounts
Content-Type: application/json

{"accountNumber":"ACC-A","currency":"USD","openingBalance":200.00}

### Open account B → 201
POST {{host}}/api/accounts
Content-Type: application/json

{"accountNumber":"ACC-B","currency":"USD","openingBalance":0.00}

### Transfer → 200 + transactionId. Pass your own correlation id and watch it echo back.
POST {{host}}/api/transfers
X-Request-Id: my-trace-123
Content-Type: application/json

{"from":"ACC-A","to":"ACC-B","amount":50.00,"description":"rent"}

### Overdraw → 422 application/problem+json {type,title,status,detail,instance}
POST {{host}}/api/transfers
Content-Type: application/json

{"from":"ACC-A","to":"ACC-B","amount":9999.00}

### Validation failure (negative amount) → 400 application/problem+json with $.errors.amount
POST {{host}}/api/transfers
Content-Type: application/json

{"from":"ACC-A","to":"ACC-B","amount":-5.00}

### Unknown account → 400 Problem Detail
POST {{host}}/api/transfers
Content-Type: application/json

{"from":"ACC-A","to":"NOPE","amount":1.00}
